# Page Object Pattern

## TypeScript (Playwright E2E)

All page objects extend `BasePage` from `e2e/pages/base.page.ts`.

```typescript
import { type Locator, expect } from "@playwright/test";
import { BasePage } from "./base.page";

export class MyPage extends BasePage {
  readonly url = "/my-page";

  // Locators as getters — use testId(), role(), label(), text() helpers
  get submitButton(): Locator {
    return this.testId("my-page-btn-submit");
  }
  get emailInput(): Locator {
    return this.label("E-posta");
  }

  // Actions return void (async)
  async fillEmail(email: string) {
    await this.emailInput.fill(email);
  }
  async submit() {
    await this.submitButton.click();
  }

  // Assertions use expect
  async assertPageLoaded() {
    await expect(this.submitButton).toBeVisible();
  }
}
```

## Python (Engine BDD)

All page objects extend `BasePage` from `engine/pages/base_page.py`.

```python
from pages.base_page import BasePage
from playwright.sync_api import Page, expect

class MyPage(BasePage):
    SUBMIT_BTN = '[data-testid="my-page-btn-submit"]'

    def __init__(self, page: Page, base_url: str = ""):
        super().__init__(page)
        self._base_url = base_url

    def submit(self):
        self.page.locator(self.SUBMIT_BTN).click()
        return self
```

## Rules

1. One file per screen, components in `components/` subfolder
2. Locators: prefer `data-testid` > `getByRole` > `getByLabel` > CSS
3. Actions: one method per user interaction
4. Assertions: separate methods, never inline in test files
5. Use `e2e/fixtures/pages.fixture.ts` for DI injection in tests
